WEBVTT

00:11.924 --> 00:15.232
[indistinct conversations]

00:22.239 --> 00:23.588
[beeps]

00:23.588 --> 00:25.068
[door unlocks]

00:38.255 --> 00:40.170
[computer whirring]

00:40.170 --> 00:41.389
[beeps]

00:41.389 --> 00:44.044
[door whooshing]

00:51.181 --> 00:53.444
[air hisses]

01:00.103 --> 01:03.976
[clicks]

01:30.177 --> 01:33.136
[man] I DARESAY YOU'VE INSPECTED
MORE MODERN FACILITIES

01:33.136 --> 01:35.138
IN YOUR TRAVELS, BUT, UH--

01:35.138 --> 01:38.881
GRIFFIN.
DON'T COME IN HERE.

01:38.881 --> 01:40.317
DR. SEBERG, WHAT'S WRONG?

01:45.235 --> 01:47.107
OH, MY GOD.

01:55.158 --> 01:58.030
[shoes shuffling]

02:01.251 --> 02:03.035
[shuffles]

02:04.341 --> 02:06.735
HEY.

02:06.735 --> 02:08.432
HEY.

02:08.432 --> 02:10.913
CHEER UP.WHY?

02:10.913 --> 02:13.045
UH, 'CAUSE IT'S BETTER
TO BE HAPPY THAN SAD.

02:13.045 --> 02:15.831
I'M NOT SAD.YOU'RE VERY SAD.

02:15.831 --> 02:19.487
YOU'VE BEEN SAD FOR MONTHS,
EVER SINCE, UH--WHAT, IS THIS SOME SORT
OF THERAPY SESSION?

02:19.487 --> 02:22.098
DID YOU BRING TISSUE
IN CASE YOU MAKE ME CRY?

02:22.098 --> 02:24.666
THERE WE GO. ZING OF ANGER--
GETS THE BLOOD UP.

02:24.666 --> 02:27.712
THAT'S A GOOD START.IS THIS WHAT YOU CAME HERE FOR--
TO ZING ME?

02:27.712 --> 02:31.151
BECAUSE I'VE GOT
PAPERWORK TO DO.JANE, CALL FOR YOU. THEY SAY
IT'S EXTREMELY URGENT. LINE TWO.

02:31.151 --> 02:33.457
OOH.

02:33.457 --> 02:35.067
[picks up telephone receiver]

02:35.067 --> 02:37.157
[clears throat]
THIS IS JANE.

02:37.157 --> 02:39.159
[woman] Good morning, Mr. Jane.

02:39.159 --> 02:42.118
MY NAME IS DR. ALICIA SEBERG.

02:42.118 --> 02:44.512
I GATHER FROM A BRIEF SEARCH
ON THE INTERNET

02:44.512 --> 02:46.601
THAT YOU'RE THE BEST DETECTIVE
IN MY IMMEDIATE VICINITY.

02:46.601 --> 02:48.429
OH. WELL, UM...

02:48.429 --> 02:52.302
YOU FLATTER ME, BUT, UH,
I'M NOT ACTUALLY A DETECTIVE.

02:52.302 --> 02:53.651
I NEED
YOUR PROFESSIONAL ASSISTANCE.

02:53.651 --> 02:55.175
Please come immediately.

02:55.175 --> 02:56.828
I'VE BEEN MURDERED.

03:07.926 --> 03:10.886
[helicopter whirring]

03:34.953 --> 03:36.520
WHOO!

03:38.827 --> 03:41.656
THAT WAS FUN!

03:41.656 --> 03:43.397
[Patrick] WHOO!

03:43.397 --> 03:47.444
AGENT LISBON! CBI!

03:47.444 --> 03:49.664
MA'AM, SIR,
PLEASE FOLLOW ME.

03:49.664 --> 03:50.882
ALL RIGHT!

03:50.882 --> 03:53.842
AGENT LISBON.
AND YOU ARE...

03:53.842 --> 03:55.757
I'M THIS GUY--
PATRICK JANE. CONSULTANT?

03:55.757 --> 03:58.673
OKAY, TERESA, PATRICK,
GLAD TO MEET YOU BOTH.

03:58.673 --> 04:01.284
I'M DEAN HARKEN, CALIFORNIA
DISEASE CONTROL AUTHORITY.

04:01.284 --> 04:03.591
NICE TO MEET YOU.YEAH, WE HAVE

04:03.591 --> 04:05.941
A POTENTIAL CODE RED
VIRUS OUTBREAK SITUATION HERE.

04:05.941 --> 04:08.726
THIS FACILITY
IS UNDER C.D.C.A. CONTROL,

04:08.726 --> 04:10.859
AS PER
STATE EMERGENCY PROTOCOLS.

04:10.859 --> 04:13.818
THOUSANDS OF PEOPLE MIGHT DIE IF
WE DON'T GET THIS RIGHT, OKAY?

04:13.818 --> 04:16.778
WE'VE BEEN APPRISED
OF THE BASIC--NOW SHE'S DENYING IT, OF COURSE,
BUT THIS SITUATION'S

04:16.778 --> 04:18.432
ALMOST CERTAINLY RESULTED
FROM AN ERROR BY DR. SEBERG.

04:18.432 --> 04:20.912
THERE'S NO CRIMINALITY
INVOLVED,

04:20.912 --> 04:23.915
SO YOU'RE NOT REALLY
NEEDED HERE.PROBABLY,
BUT WE'RE GONNA HAVE--

04:23.915 --> 04:26.701
AS A PROFESSIONAL COURTESY, I'M
GONNA LET YOU INTO THE FACILITY.

04:26.701 --> 04:29.181
I'M HAPPY FOR YOU GUYS
TO OBSERVE AND GATHER EVIDENCE,

04:29.181 --> 04:32.184
AS LONG AS YOU REMEMBER
THAT C.D.C.A. IS BIG DOG HERE.

04:32.184 --> 04:35.187
OUR INVESTIGATION HAS PRIORITY.
NOW ARE WE COOL WITH THAT?

04:35.187 --> 04:36.319
ABSOLUTELY.

04:36.319 --> 04:38.539
CAN I SEE
YOUR I.D. ALSO?

04:38.539 --> 04:40.628
SURE.

04:42.282 --> 04:45.937
THANK YOU... DEAN.

04:45.937 --> 04:49.724
NO PICTURE. THAT'S A SHAME.
YOU'RE A GOOD-LOOKING MAN.

04:49.724 --> 04:52.204
SCOTT PRICE,
I MANAGE THIS FACILITY

04:52.204 --> 04:53.815
FOR ZITEK
BIOSYSTEMS DIVISION.

04:53.815 --> 04:55.512
RIGHT OFF THE BAT,
LET ME ASSURE YOU

04:55.512 --> 04:58.907
THAT WE AS A COMPANY ARE
110% COMMITTED TO GIVING YOU

04:58.907 --> 05:02.389
THE BEST POSSIBLE COOPERATION.THANK YOU, MR. PRICE. SHALL WE?
THERE'S A SENSE OF URGENCY HERE.

05:02.389 --> 05:05.696
AH, YES, OF COURSE.

05:05.696 --> 05:08.046
LISBON, JANE, DR. EDMUNDS,
HEAD OF RESEARCH HERE.

05:08.046 --> 05:10.048
HE'LL TAKE YOU
TO THE RELEASE INCIDENT.

05:10.048 --> 05:12.790
PRICE, COME WITH ME.

05:12.790 --> 05:14.792
THANK YOU FOR COMING
SO QUICKLY.

05:14.792 --> 05:17.186
WHAT EXACTLY IS IT
THAT YOU DO HERE?

05:17.186 --> 05:18.796
BIOWARFARE.
WITH MODERN TECHNOLOGY,

05:18.796 --> 05:21.321
ANTHRAX, BOTULISM,
BUBONIC PLAGUE,

05:21.321 --> 05:24.106
EVEN COBRA VENOM ALL HAVE
STRONG WEAPONIZING POTENTIAL.

05:24.106 --> 05:26.761
IT'S A GROWING FIELD.
A LOT OF EXCITING DEVELOPMENTS.

05:26.761 --> 05:29.329
YOU DEVELOP WAYS OF KILLING
PEOPLE IN LARGE NUMBERS.

05:29.329 --> 05:31.722
TO THE CONTRARY. WE DEVELOP
ANTIDOTES, WAYS TO COMBAT

05:31.722 --> 05:33.855
THE THINGS THAT KILL
LARGE NUMBERS OF PEOPLE.

05:33.855 --> 05:35.465
HERE WE ARE.

05:35.465 --> 05:39.817
[computer whirring]

05:39.817 --> 05:41.210
[beeps]

05:41.210 --> 05:42.690
[door unlocks]FOLLOW ME.

05:45.606 --> 05:48.086
120.

05:48.086 --> 05:51.568
DARLING. IS THIS MR. JANE?

05:51.568 --> 05:54.397
YES. HOW ARE YOU FEELING?THE SAME.

05:54.397 --> 05:56.399
INTERESTING IMPROVEMENT
IN CARDIAC RATE, THOUGH.

05:56.399 --> 06:00.055
MY METABOLISM'S TRYING TO
FIGHT BACK WITH ADRENALINE.

06:00.055 --> 06:02.100
GOOD MORNING, MR. JANE.

06:02.100 --> 06:03.972
HI.

06:03.972 --> 06:05.756
AGENT LISBON, CBI.

06:07.497 --> 06:09.891
YOU MIND WRITING THIS DOWN
FOR US?

06:09.891 --> 06:13.851
SOMEONE OPENED THIS FLASK
AND LEFT IT UNDER THE TANK.

06:13.851 --> 06:17.072
IT CONTAINS AN AIRBORNE FORM
OF CRYPTOHANSA B STRAIN.

06:17.072 --> 06:19.379
IT'S
AN ENGINEERED SUPERVIRUS.

06:19.379 --> 06:22.120
IF IT ESCAPED FROM THIS ROOM,
IT WOULD KILL

06:22.120 --> 06:24.558
EVERY VERTEBRATE CREATURE
WITHIN A QUARTER-MILE RADIUS.

06:24.558 --> 06:27.648
IT ATTACKS THE RED BLOOD CELLS,
GRADUALLY STOPS THEM

06:27.648 --> 06:29.693
FROM DELIVERING OXYGEN.

06:29.693 --> 06:31.956
THE VICTIM... DIES FROM
SUFFOCATION OR A HEART ATTACK,

06:31.956 --> 06:34.089
DEPENDING ON
THEIR PHYSICAL CONDITION.

06:34.089 --> 06:35.873
HOW LONG AFTER EXPOSURE?

06:35.873 --> 06:38.615
WE ESTIMATE ANYWHERE
FROM TWO TO SIX HOURS.

06:38.615 --> 06:42.750
SO YOU COULD DIE AT ANY TIME?YES.

06:42.750 --> 06:45.361
HARKEN SAYS YOU DID THIS
YOURSELF--TRAGIC ERROR.

06:45.361 --> 06:48.364
HE'S A BUREAUCRAT. HE'S LOOKING
FOR THE EASY ANSWER.

06:48.364 --> 06:50.845
IT TAKES FOUR DISTINCT STEPS
TO REMOVE A CAP

06:50.845 --> 06:53.804
FROM ONE OF THESE FLASKS,
AND WE NEVER OPEN A FLASK

06:53.804 --> 06:56.154
OUTSIDE OF THE TANK.
THAT'S JUST BASIC.

06:56.154 --> 07:00.028
I CAN ASSURE YOU BOTH,
I HAD NOTHING TO DO WITH THIS.

07:00.028 --> 07:03.335
BUT THIS WAS NO MISTAKE.
WHOEVER DID THIS WANTED ME DEAD.

07:03.335 --> 07:05.642
EVERYBODY KNOWS I TAKE
THE FIRST SHIFT.

07:05.642 --> 07:08.906
SHE CALLED YOU "DARLING."
YOU BOTH HAVE WEDDING BANDS.

07:08.906 --> 07:10.778
YOU HUSBAND AND WIFE?

07:10.778 --> 07:12.519
YES.

07:14.172 --> 07:15.957
WELL, SHE LOOKS SURPRISED

07:15.957 --> 07:18.786
BECAUSE YOU SEEM
INCREDIBLY CALM AND COOL

07:18.786 --> 07:20.657
FOR A MAN WHOSE WIFE
IS DYING.

07:20.657 --> 07:24.139
HOW WOULD AN ABSENCE OF CALM
AND COOL BE USEFUL TO HER?

07:24.139 --> 07:26.271
GOOD POINT.
CORRECT ME IF I'M WRONG,

07:26.271 --> 07:28.448
BUT FOR THE KILLER TO OPEN
THE FLASK,

07:28.448 --> 07:30.798
THEY WOULD HAVE TO EXPOSE
THEMSELVES TO THE VIRUS,

07:30.798 --> 07:34.149
IN WHICH CASE, THEY WOULD BE
DYING OR POSSIBLY DEAD ALREADY.

07:34.149 --> 07:36.630
NO, THERE'S AN ANTIDOTE.

07:36.630 --> 07:38.675
IT'S AN ENZYME COMPOUND.

07:38.675 --> 07:41.635
IF TAKEN BEFORE EXPOSURE,
IT PREVENTS INFECTION.

07:41.635 --> 07:43.985
I ASSUME WHOEVER DID THIS
TOOK A DOSE.

07:43.985 --> 07:47.336
COULDN'T YOU J--NO, I CAN'T TAKE IT NOW.

07:47.336 --> 07:51.209
THE ANTIDOTE ONLY WORKS IF TAKEN
BEFOREEXPOSURE, AS I SAID.

07:51.209 --> 07:53.951
WHY DIDN'T YOU TAKE IT BEFORE,
JUST AS A PRECAUTION?

07:53.951 --> 07:57.128
THE SIDE EFFECTS OF REGULAR USE
ARE FAR TOO SEVERE.

07:57.128 --> 07:59.217
WHO ELSE HAD ACCESS
TO THE VIRUS FLASK?

07:59.217 --> 08:01.698
THE ONLY PEOPLE ALLOWED
IN THE LAB ARE CLIFF AND I,

08:01.698 --> 08:04.135
WELKS, NASH AND TRIPP,
OUR COLLEAGUES.

08:04.135 --> 08:06.616
WE HAVE A STATE-OF-THE-ART
BIOMETRIC SECURITY SYSTEM,

08:06.616 --> 08:08.096
AS YOU CAN SEE.

08:08.096 --> 08:11.055
SO YOUR HUSBAND
OR ONE OF THE THREE COLLEAGUES

08:11.055 --> 08:12.883
IS THE KILLER.

08:14.319 --> 08:17.497
SORRY. UH, WILLBE THE KILLER.

08:17.497 --> 08:19.281
JANE.

08:19.281 --> 08:20.412
I'M JUST... MM.

08:22.240 --> 08:25.374
THAT'S ALL RIGHT. THAT IS
THE UNAVOIDABLE CONCLUSION.

08:25.374 --> 08:27.028
YES.

08:27.028 --> 08:29.596
WHERE ARE
THE OTHER THREE NOW?

08:29.596 --> 08:33.034
HARKEN IS HAVING THEM
FILL OUT AN ACCIDENT REPORT.WE'RE GONNA NEED TO SPEAK
TO THEM.

08:33.034 --> 08:35.471
OOH, THIS IS
A GOOD ONE, EH?

08:35.471 --> 08:37.299
GOOD?

08:37.299 --> 08:39.562
WELL, INTERESTING. UNIQUE.

08:39.562 --> 08:43.566
IF YOU'RE A JADED, GHOULISH
ADVENTURE SEEKER.

08:43.566 --> 08:45.960
GHOULISH? LISTEN, IF PEOPLE
ARE GONNA KILL EACH OTHER

08:45.960 --> 08:48.571
AND WE HAVE TO CATCH THEM,
I WOULD MUCH RATHER

08:48.571 --> 08:50.921
THEY GO ABOUT IT WITH
SOME KIND OF ORIGINALITY.

08:50.921 --> 08:52.749
[Van Pelt] Boss?HEY, VAN PELT.

08:52.749 --> 08:55.143
I need you to do background
checks on Cliff Edmunds...

08:55.143 --> 08:58.102
[speaking indistinctly]LILITH NASH,
GRIFFIN LATIMER WELKS,

08:58.102 --> 08:59.800
Florian Eric Tripp.

08:59.800 --> 09:01.497
I'm sending you
their details now.

09:01.497 --> 09:04.500
ANYTHING TO BE
LOOKING OUT FOR IN PARTICULAR?

09:04.500 --> 09:06.763
OH, UH, ONE OF THEM RELEASED
A LETHAL SUPERVIRUS

09:06.763 --> 09:08.504
THAT COULD KILL HALF
THE STATE OF CALIFORNIA,

09:08.504 --> 09:10.201
so I guess we're looking for

09:10.201 --> 09:12.900
someone with a prior background
as an evil supervillain.

09:12.900 --> 09:14.292
OKAY.

09:16.599 --> 09:19.689
THAT LAST PART WAS A JOKE.YEAH, WE GET IT.

09:19.689 --> 09:20.951
Later.

09:30.482 --> 09:32.006
HELLO.

09:32.006 --> 09:33.224
HI.

09:33.224 --> 09:34.530
HELLO.HELLO.

09:38.403 --> 09:40.580
[clears throat]

09:42.190 --> 09:44.975
[sighs deeply]

09:44.975 --> 09:48.196
WHAT ARE YOU DOIN'?WHAT DOES IT LOOK LIKE
I'M DOING?

09:48.196 --> 09:52.722
TRYING TO MAKE US NERVOUS?CORRECT. HOW AM I DOING?

09:52.722 --> 09:55.116
DOING WELL.EXCELLENT.

09:55.116 --> 09:57.292
BUT WHY?

09:57.292 --> 10:00.034
ONE OF YOU THREE
MURDERED ALICIA SEBERG,

10:00.034 --> 10:04.038
OR HER HUSBAND DID.
IT'S OUR JOB TO FIND OUT WHO.AND WE'RE IN A HURRY,

10:04.038 --> 10:08.129
AND NERVOUS PEOPLE
ARE EASY TO READ.AND WHAT DO YOU GATHER
FROM ALL THIS READING?

10:08.129 --> 10:10.218
WELL, YOU'RE AN OPEN BOOK.
YOU'RE EXACTLY WHAT

10:10.218 --> 10:12.742
YOU SEEM TO BE--
A STRAIGHT ARROW, A BOY SCOUT.

10:12.742 --> 10:15.527
AM I RIGHT?NO.

10:15.527 --> 10:18.400
I'M WRONG.
THERE'S A HIDDEN SIDE TO YOU.YES, BUT--

10:18.400 --> 10:20.532
WHAT ARE YOU HIDING?NOTHING.

10:20.532 --> 10:22.665
WHAT IS HE HIDING, LILITH?I DON'T KNOW.

10:22.665 --> 10:24.232
WHAT ARE YOUHIDING?I-I'M NOT--

10:24.232 --> 10:25.799
IT WAS YOU, WASN'T IT?ME WHAT?

10:25.799 --> 10:28.715
YOU WERE HAVING AN AFFAIR
WITH ALICIA SEBERG.

10:28.715 --> 10:30.934
WHAT? NO, NOT WITH ME.

10:30.934 --> 10:34.764
NOT WITH YOU.
WITH WHO, THEN?

10:34.764 --> 10:36.766
I OVERSEE EQUIPMENT
AND INVENTORY,

10:36.766 --> 10:38.899
NOT MY COLLEAGUES'
PRIVATE LIVES.

10:38.899 --> 10:40.770
BUT SHE WASHAVING
AN AFFAIR, HUH?

10:40.770 --> 10:43.773
WHY ELSE WOULD A HUSBAND
HAVE THE MOTIVES TO KILL HER?

10:43.773 --> 10:46.733
AND IF IT WASN'T HER HUSBAND,
IT WAS ONE OF YOU.

10:46.733 --> 10:48.256
WHO WAS IT?

10:51.868 --> 10:53.565
MY GUESS...

10:55.655 --> 10:57.613
KASEEM.[knocks on table]

10:57.613 --> 10:59.702
YES.

10:59.702 --> 11:01.486
DOES HER HUSBAND KNOW?OH, HE KNOWS.

11:01.486 --> 11:03.097
DR. EDMUNDS IS

11:03.097 --> 11:05.665
A KIND, GENTLE MAN.
HE COULDN'T HAVE DONE THIS.

11:05.665 --> 11:08.319
THANK YOU, LILITH, FLORIAN...

11:08.319 --> 11:09.756
GRIFFIN.

11:19.069 --> 11:22.377
WHY DIDN'T YOU TELL US YOU WERE
HAVING AN AFFAIR

11:22.377 --> 11:25.075
WITH DR. KASEEM HERE?BECAUSE IT ISN'T RELEVANT.

11:25.075 --> 11:27.643
YEAH, WE HAVE
AN HONEST AND OPEN MARRIAGE.

11:27.643 --> 11:28.949
THEY DO.

11:28.949 --> 11:30.777
REALLY?
YOU DON'T MIND?

11:30.777 --> 11:32.692
[Edmunds]
NO, I DON'T MIND AT ALL.

11:32.692 --> 11:34.519
FIDELITY IS SIMPLY
A CULTURAL CONVENTION.

11:34.519 --> 11:37.044
LIKE CLOTHES
AND NOT KILLING PEOPLE.

11:37.044 --> 11:39.263
YOU COULD SAY SO.

11:39.263 --> 11:42.658
COME ON.
IT MUST BUG YOU A LITTLE.

11:42.658 --> 11:47.184
NO. WE LOVE EACH OTHER.
HER HAPPINESS IS MINE.

11:47.184 --> 11:50.405
IT'S NOT LIKE I DON'T HAVE
AFFAIRS MYSELF.

11:50.405 --> 11:53.060
ARE YOU HAVING AN AFFAIR
PRESENTLY?

11:53.060 --> 11:55.584
NO. I'VE BEEN FAR TOO BUSY.

11:55.584 --> 11:58.500
Y-YOU MUST THINK
THIS IS A LITTLE WEIRD.

11:58.500 --> 12:02.722
UH... YEAH... AT FIRST.

12:02.722 --> 12:04.549
BUT HEY. [chuckles]

12:04.549 --> 12:05.942
BUT HEY. [chuckles]

12:05.942 --> 12:09.163
WHAT AN ELOQUENT PHRASE
THAT IS.

12:11.121 --> 12:12.688
[telephone rings]

12:12.688 --> 12:15.038
OH! ISABEL. THANK GOD.

12:15.038 --> 12:16.474
[ring]

12:16.474 --> 12:17.562
[ring]

12:17.562 --> 12:21.741
[choking][ring]

12:21.741 --> 12:25.701
Mom?
Mom, I got Dad's message.

12:25.701 --> 12:27.616
[mouths words] Is it true?

12:27.616 --> 12:29.009
YES, IT'S TRUE.

12:29.009 --> 12:30.880
[crying] No.

12:30.880 --> 12:32.534
No, no, it can't be!

12:32.534 --> 12:34.536
OH, THIS IS A PICKLE,
ISN'T IT?

12:34.536 --> 12:37.974
[crying] OH, BABY, DON'T CRY.
DON'T CRY.

12:37.974 --> 12:40.977
[continues crying] How can you
tell me not to cry?

12:40.977 --> 12:44.720
Of course I'm going to cry.
Is there something you can do?

12:44.720 --> 12:48.376
There has to be something!

12:48.376 --> 12:50.552
LISTEN TO ME.

12:50.552 --> 12:52.554
WE DON'T HAVE MUCH TIME,

12:52.554 --> 12:55.339
SO WE MUSTN'T WASTE IT
WEEPING AND WAILING, OKAY?

12:55.339 --> 12:57.080
Okay.GOOD.

12:57.080 --> 13:01.781
HOW'S SCHOOL GOING? DID YOU GET
YOUR CALCULUS GRADE UP?

13:01.781 --> 13:04.348
I got a 95 on my last test.

13:04.348 --> 13:07.787
OH, WELL DONE.
YOU KEEP THAT UP.

13:07.787 --> 13:12.052
A-AND WHAT ABOUT THAT BOY, ANDY?
HOW'S THAT GOING?

13:12.052 --> 13:15.751
Oh, he's a jerk. [sniffles]
I don't see him anymore.

13:15.751 --> 13:18.362
WELL, I MUST SAY,
I'M GLAD TO HEAR THAT.

13:18.362 --> 13:20.625
I DIDN'T LIKE
THE SOUND OF HIM.

13:20.625 --> 13:23.324
[coughs]

13:23.324 --> 13:26.414
[choking]

13:26.414 --> 13:28.808
I LOVE YOU SO MUCH.

13:28.808 --> 13:32.637
[whispers] YOU'RE THE BEST THING
I EVER DID.

13:32.637 --> 13:36.685
AND I AM SO... PROUD OF YOU.

13:36.685 --> 13:39.253
[crying] Mom.

13:39.253 --> 13:40.776
SHH, SHH, SHH!

13:40.776 --> 13:43.344
WHEN I'M GONE,

13:43.344 --> 13:46.347
YOU MUSTN'T WASTE TIME
BEING SAD.

13:46.347 --> 13:50.699
A LITTLE WHILE IS OKAY,
BUT NOT TOO LONG.

13:50.699 --> 13:54.398
YOU BE BRAVE.

13:54.398 --> 13:56.487
AND BE HAPPY.

13:56.487 --> 13:59.099
[crying]

13:59.099 --> 14:01.623
BYE, BABY.

14:01.623 --> 14:04.234
[sobbing] Mom!

14:04.234 --> 14:06.280
Mom!BYE, BABY.

14:06.280 --> 14:07.803
No, Mom!

14:07.803 --> 14:10.980
[gasping]

14:10.980 --> 14:12.634
GOOD-BYE, MY LOVE.

14:12.634 --> 14:14.854
I LOVE YOU, DARLING.
GOOD-BYE.

14:14.854 --> 14:18.118
[gasping]

14:18.118 --> 14:20.468
[clank]

14:20.468 --> 14:22.339
[chokes]

14:27.301 --> 14:31.609
[sobbing]

14:31.609 --> 14:33.394
SHE'S GONE, BABY.

14:33.394 --> 14:35.004
SHE'S GONE.

14:35.004 --> 14:37.877
[continues sobbing]

14:44.796 --> 14:48.757
[indistinct conversations]

14:48.757 --> 14:50.063
SHE'S DEAD?

14:50.063 --> 14:51.629
[Lisbon] YES.

14:53.849 --> 14:55.024
I'M, UH...

14:57.026 --> 14:59.072
I'M SORRY FOR YOUR LOSS.

15:03.467 --> 15:05.730
